\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 1. 
\f3\fs30\fsmilli15210 fonts
\f0\fs28 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 This 
\f0\b directory
\f1\b0  contains font files with the 
\f0\b .fnt
\f1\b0  extension, which we simply transfer into the 
\f2\fs26 fonts
\f1\fs24  
\f0\b directory
\f1\b0  on the iPod running Rockbox.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 2. 
\f3\fs30\fsmilli15210 icons
\f0\fs28 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The "iPodOS" theme uses default icons, so we don't even need to transfer them to the iPod because they are already present in the firmware files, and their names and references are identical.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 3. 
\f3\fs30\fsmilli15210 themes
\f0\fs28 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 This 
\f0\b directory
\f1\b0  stores a file with the 
\f0\b .cfg
\f1\b0  extension. It can be customized or simply viewed using a text editor, such as 
\f0\b Visual Studio Code (VSC)
\f1\b0 . We transfer this file to the 
\f2\fs26 themes
\f1\fs24  
\f0\b directory
\f1\b0  on the iPod with Rockbox. (We will be interacting with it later).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 4. 
\f3\fs30\fsmilli15210 wps
\f0\fs28 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

